<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><h3>November 2021</h3><div name="1.GoverningTexts" data-unique="1.GoverningTexts"></div><h2>1. Governing Texts</h2><div name="1.1.Legislation" data-unique="1.1.Legislation"></div><h3>1.1. Legislation</h3><ul><li>Articles 37-39 of the&nbsp;<a href="https://platform.dataguidance.com/cross-border-charts/general-data-protection-regulation" target="_blank">General Data Protection Regulation (Regulation (EU) 2016/679)</a> ('GDPR')</li><li>Articles 57 and 103 of the Act No.78-17 of 6 January 1978 on Data Processing, Data Files and Individual Liberties (as amended to implement the GDPR) (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/la-loi-informatique-et-libertes" target="_blank">here</a>) ('the Act')</li><li>Article 30 of Law No. 2018-493 of 20 June 2018 on the Protection of Personal Data (only available in French <a href="https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do;jsessionid=DD965092410B9E367833F2115EDBDB80.tplgfr31s_1?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000037085952&amp;dateTexte=&amp;oldAction=rechJO&amp;categorieLien=id&amp;idJO=JORFCONT000037085949" target="_blank">here</a>) ('the Law')</li><li>Decree No. 2019-536 of 29 May 2019 enacted for the application of the Act No. 78-17 of 6 January 1978 on data processing, data files and individual liberties (only available in French <a href="https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000038528420&amp;categorieLien=id" target="_blank">here</a>) ('the Decree')</li></ul><div name="1.2.Regulatoryauthorityguidance" data-unique="1.2.Regulatoryauthorityguidance"></div><h3>1.2. Regulatory authority guidance</h3><p>The <a href="http://ec.europa.eu/newsroom/article29/news.cfm?item_type=1358" target="_blank">Article 29 Working Party</a>&nbsp;('WP29')&nbsp;has issued the following guidance:</p><ul><li><a href="https://platform.dataguidance.com/legal-research/guidelines-data-protection-officers-dpos-wp-243-rev01-5-april-2017" target="_blank">Guidelines on Data Protection Officers</a>&nbsp;('DPOs') (adopted on 13 December 2016, as revised and adopted on 5 April 2017) ('the Guidelines'); and</li><li><a href="https://platform.dataguidance.com/legal-research/faqs-data-protection-officers-dpos-wp-243-13-december-2016" target="_blank">Frequently Asked Questions</a> ('the FAQs').</li></ul><p>The <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/" target="_blank">European Data Protection Board</a>&nbsp;('EDPB') has replaced the WP29. The EDPB has endorsed the Guidelines.&nbsp;</p><p>The <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/professionnel" target="_blank">French data protection authority</a> ('CNIL'<u>)</u> has issued the following guidance:</p><ul><li>Become a DPO (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/devenir-delegue-la-protection-des-donnees" target="_blank">here</a>);</li><li>DPO Certification (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/certification-des-competences-du-dpo-0" target="_blank">here</a>);</li><li>Appoint a DPO (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/designation-dpo" target="_blank">here</a>);</li><li>DPO: where to start? (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/dpo-par-ou-commencer" target="_blank">here</a>); and</li><li>Appoint a DPO in communities (only available in French <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/designer-un-delegue-la-protection-des-donnees-dans-une-collectivite" target="_blank">here</a>) ('the DPO in Public Entities Guidance'). Please note that this guidance refers to DPOs appointed by public entities.</li></ul><div name="2.Definitions" data-unique="2.Definitions"></div><h2>2. Definitions</h2><p><strong>Data protection officer:</strong>&nbsp;There is no definition of DPO in the GDPR, nor the Act.</p><p><strong>Data controller:</strong> The natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which, alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data; where the purposes and means of such processing are determined by EU or Member State law, the controller or the specific criteria for its nomination may be provided for by EU or Member State law (Article 4(7) of the GDPR).</p><p><strong>Data processor:</strong> A natural or legal person, public authority, agency or any other body which processes personal data on behalf of the controller (Article 4(8) of the GDPR).</p><div name="3.DPOAppointment" data-unique="3.DPOAppointment"></div><h2>3. DPO Appointment</h2><div name="3.1.Required" data-unique="3.1.Required"></div><h3><a id="column-1" name="column-1"></a><a id="column-2" name="column-2"></a>3.1. Required</h3><p>There are no national variations.</p><div name="3.2.Recommended" data-unique="3.2.Recommended"></div><h3><a id="column-3" name="column-3"></a>3.2. Recommended</h3><p>There are no national variations.</p><div name="3.3.Beneficialregime" data-unique="3.3.Beneficialregime"></div><h3><a id="column-4" name="column-4"></a>3.3. Beneficial regime</h3><p>There are no national variations.</p><div name="4.DPOSpecified" data-unique="4.DPOSpecified"></div><h2>4. DPO Specified</h2><div name="4.1.Role" data-unique="4.1.Role"></div><h3><a id="column-5" name="column-5"></a>4.1. Role</h3><p>The DPO (Articles 48 and 49 of the Decree):</p><ul><li>must keep a list of the processing carried out, which is immediately accessible to any person applying for access; such list shall be drawn up within three months from his/her appointment; and</li><li>must be consulted, prior to their implementation, on all new processing of personal data required to be included in the list of automated processing activities of the controller.</li></ul><p>In addition, in the context of public entities, DPOs should communicate with their legal representatives responsible for compliance with processing operations, which can be the mayor or president of the regional council, as well as the operational department responsible for implementing the processing (the DPO in Public Entities Guidance).</p><div name="4.2.Professionalqualifications" data-unique="4.2.Professionalqualifications"></div><h3><a id="column-6" name="column-6"></a>4.2. Professional qualifications</h3><p>Deliberation No. 2018-318 of 20 September 2018 Adopting the Criteria of the Standard of Qualification of the DPO (only available in French <a href="https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do;jsessionid=46002F5EFD8F35A73251FDC7949EEDB6.tplgfr26s_2?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000037485691&amp;dateTexte=&amp;oldAction=rechJO&amp;categorieLien=id&amp;idJO=JORFCONT000037485359" target="_blank">here</a>) ('Deliberation No. 2018-318') adopted criteria standards on the certification reference system, setting out a list of 17 required competencies to be certified as a DPO, including:</p><ul><li>the DPO must understand the principles of, for example, lawful processing, data minimisation, data accuracy, and data retention;</li><li>the DPO must be able to identify the legal basis of a processing activity;</li><li>the DPO must be able to organise and participate in data protection audits;</li><li>the candidate must know how to identify personal data breaches which require notification to CNIL and data subjects; and</li><li>the DPO must know whether or not it is necessary to carry out a DPIA.</li></ul><p>Deliberation No. 2018-317 of 20 September 2018 Adopting the Criteria of the Reference Framework of Accreditation of Certification Bodies for the Certification of the Competences of the DPO (only available in French <a href="https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do;jsessionid=46002F5EFD8F35A73251FDC7949EEDB6.tplgfr26s_2?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000037485671&amp;dateTexte=&amp;oldAction=rechJO&amp;categorieLien=id&amp;idJO=JORFCONT000037485359" target="_blank">here</a>) adopts the accreditation framework, setting out the criteria for organisations who wish to be certified by CNIL to certify DPOs according to the provisions of Deliberation No. 2018-318.</p><div name="5.AdditionalRequirements" data-unique="5.AdditionalRequirements"></div><h2>5. Additional Requirements</h2><div name="5.1.Notification" data-unique="5.1.Notification"></div><h3><a id="column-7" name="column-7"></a>5.1. Notification</h3><p>The notification to CNIL can be done online in four steps, only available in French, <a href="https://designations.cnil.fr/dpo/designation/organisme.designant.delegue.action" target="_blank">here</a>.</p><div name="5.2.Location" data-unique="5.2.Location"></div><h3><a id="column-8" name="column-8"></a>5.2. Location</h3><p>There are no national variations.</p><div name="5.3.Other" data-unique="5.3.Other"></div><h3><a id="column-9" name="column-9"></a>5.3. Other</h3><p>There are no national variations.</p><div name="6.Penalties" data-unique="6.Penalties"></div><h2>6. Penalties</h2><p>There are no national variations.</p></div></div></div>